column1: :has_definition ""A planet which is formed as a result of a gas giant's hydrogen and helium atmosphere, as well as its outer layers, being stripped away by a stellar wind through photoevaporation and hydrodynamic escape.""

,A chthonian planet, also known exactly as a cthonian planet, is a type of planet that is the same as something which is both a planet and derives from a giant gas planet, and also formed as a result of an intersection between processes including photoevaporation and hydrodynamic escape, and at least causally downstream of or within a stellar wind. Specifically, a chthonian planet is defined as a planet formed from the remnants of a gas giant whose hydrogen and helium atmosphere, along with its outer layers, are stripped away by stellar wind through mechanisms such as photoevaporation and hydrodynamic escape. This makes a chthonian planet a subtype of planets that originate from giant gas planets and are shaped by these specific cosmic phenomena.",6,True
:has_definition ""A process during which energetic radiation ionises gas and causes it to disperse away from the ionising source."" .

,Photoevaporation is a type of material transport process that involves at least some electromagnetic radiation and has gaseous environmental material as a participant. It is defined as a process during which energetic radiation ionizes gas and causes it to disperse away from the ionizing source.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001147,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A gas planet which has an atmosphere composed primarily of helium."" .

,A helium planet is the same as an entity that is both a gas planet and has at least a part that is an intersection of having an atmosphere and being composed primarily of helium molecular entities. It is classified as a type of gas planet and also as a type that has at least a part of its atmosphere primarily made of helium molecular entities. Moreover, a helium planet is defined as a gas planet which possesses an atmosphere primarily composed of helium.",4,True

:has_definition ""An astronomical body which 1) is held together by its own gravity, 2)  can attract other, similar bodies through mutual gravitational influence, and 3) has orbital dynamics that are not significantly affected by gas drag."" .

,A planetesimal is a type of astronomical body that is characterized by three key attributes: 1) it is held together by its own gravity, 2) it can attract other, similar bodies through mutual gravitational influence, and 3) its orbital dynamics are not significantly affected by gas drag.",2,True

:has_definition ""An astronomical object that forms within a protoplanetary disc when planetesimals and other solid debris aggregate and, due to gravitational forces,  fuse and initiate internal melting to produce a differentiated interior.""

,A protoplanet is a type of astronomical body defined as an astronomical object that forms within a protoplanetary disc when planetesimals and other solid debris aggregate and, due to gravitational forces, fuse and initiate internal melting to produce a differentiated interior. Moreover, it is exactly synonymous with the term ""planetary embryo.""",3,True
:has_definition ""An astronomical object which is composed of dense gas and dust rotating around a young newly formed star, a T Tauri star, or a Herbig Ae/Be star in a disk-shaped configuration."" .

,A protoplanetary disk is defined as an astronomical object composed of dense gas and dust rotating around a young newly formed star, a T Tauri star, or a Herbig Ae/Be star in a disk-shaped configuration. It is characterized as being the same as something that at least contains a part which is an intersection of gaseous environmental material and something that is notably dense. This definition also aligns with protoplanetary disks being a type of astronomical object, specifically a type that includes parts with the intersection of gaseous environmental material and elements that are considerably dense.",4,True
:has_definition ""A protoplanetary disk which is externally illuminated and undergoing photoevaporation.""

,Proplyd, a type of protoplanetary disk, is the same as something that participates in photoevaporation. It is defined as a protoplanetary disk which is externally illuminated and undergoing photoevaporation. Additionally, proplyd is exactly synonymous with an ionized protoplanetary disk.",5,True
:has_definition ""A planet which is smaller than Mercury but larger than Ceres."" .
,A mesoplanet is defined as a planet that is smaller than Mercury but larger than Ceres, categorizing it as a specific type of planet.",2,True

,A circumbinary planet is a type of planet defined as a planet which orbits two stars.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001154,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

:has_definition ""A material which is composed primarily of chemical elements and compounds with relatively low boiling points, equilibrium condensation temperatures below 1300 Kelvin, and which are part of the crust or atmosphere of a moon or planet.""

,Volatile astrogeological material is classified as a type of environmental material and is also a subset of materials that pertain to either the atmosphere or the planetary crust. It is defined as a material primarily composed of chemical elements and compounds that have relatively low boiling points and equilibrium condensation temperatures below 1300 Kelvin, and which are found in the crust or atmosphere of a moon or planet. Additionally, volatile astrogeological material is related to and can be synonymously referred to as ""volatile.""",4,True
:has_definition ""An astrogeological volatile which is composed primarily of chemical compounds with boiling points around those of hydrogen and helium.""

,Astrogeological gas is a type of volatile astrogeological material, defined as an astrogeological volatile composed primarily of chemical compounds with boiling points around those of hydrogen and helium. Additionally, it is related to the synonym ""gas.""",3,True

:has_definition ""A material which is composed primarily of chemical elements and compounds which have equilibrium condensation temperatures above approximately 1300 Kelvin and which are part of the crust or atmosphere of a moon or planet.""

,Refractory astrogeological material is a type of environmental material defined as a material primarily composed of chemical elements and compounds with equilibrium condensation temperatures above approximately 1300 Kelvin. These materials are part of the crust or atmosphere of a moon or planet. Additionally, refractory astrogeological material is synonymously related to refractory material.",3,True
:has_definition ""A process during which gases that constitute a planetary atmosphere escape that planet's gravitational field and move away into outer space."" .

,Atmospheric escape can be defined as a process during which gases that constitute a planetary atmosphere escape that planet's gravitational field and move into outer space. It is identified as a specific type of material transport process that involves several key characteristics. These characteristics include being a part of electromagnetic radiation, involving gaseous environmental material as a participant, and having both an input and an output that consists of gaseous environmental material. The input of atmospheric escape is an intersection of gaseous environmental material and a part of some planetary atmosphere, while its output is an intersection of gaseous environmental material that is located in outer space. This illustrates how atmospheric escape is closely linked to the movement of gases from a planet's atmosphere to the external environment of outer space.",7,True

:has_definition ""An atmospheric escape process during which atoms that are parts of a planetary atmosphere escape into outer space through numerous collisions with lighter atoms in that atmosphere."" .

,Hydrodynamic escape is a type of atmospheric escape, defined as an atmospheric escape process during which atoms that are parts of a planetary atmosphere escape into outer space through numerous collisions with lighter atoms in that atmosphere.",2,True
:has_definition ""A cloud which is cirriform and is formed by condensation events centred on an aircraft's contrail."" .

,A cirrus homogenitus cloud is both a type of cirrus cloud and a type of homogenitus cloud. It is defined as a cloud that is cirriform and formed by condensation events centered on an aircraft's contrail.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001160,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

:has_definition ""A cloud which 1) has been shaped into detached fibrous filaments, 2) is almost exclusively composed of ice crystals, 3) is located in the high level of the atmosphere (high étage).""@en

,A cirrus cloud is a type of ice mass and a water-based cloud that exists at least partially within some high atmospheric level and has filamentous qualities. It is primarily composed of an object aggregate that intersects with water ice crystals. The definition of a cirrus cloud is a cloud that 1) has been shaped into detached fibrous filaments, 2) is almost exclusively composed of ice crystals, and 3) is located in the high level of the atmosphere (high étage). Cirrus cloud has exact synonyms such as (Eis)-Federwolke, Cirruswolke, and Zirruswolke.",9,True

:has_definition ""An IUCN protected area in which human visitation, use and impacts are strictly controlled and limited to ensure protection and conservation of natural biodiversity and/or geodiversity, natural ecosystem assemblages and processes, and any associated cultural and spiritual values."" .

,An IUCN strict nature reserve is a type of area protected according to IUCN guidelines, which is defined as an IUCN protected area in which human visitation, use, and impacts are strictly controlled and limited to ensure the protection and conservation of natural biodiversity and/or geodiversity, natural ecosystem assemblages and processes, and any associated cultural and spiritual values. Moreover, it is broadly synonymous with a strict nature reserve.",3,True

:has_definition ""An IUCN protected area which 1) is dominated by natural ecosystems, 2) is sufficiently large to allow those ecosystems to function and develop without local anthropogenic perturbation, 3) is  managed to prevent perturbations by proximate or local anthropisation, including those caused by local and/or indigenous human communities or human visitation.""

,An IUCN wilderness area, synonymous with wilderness area, is a type of area safeguarded in accordance with IUCN guidelines. It is characterized by overlapping at least partially with the intersection of the planetary surface and areas primarily composed of natural environments. The definition of an IUCN wilderness area stipulates that it 1) is dominated by natural ecosystems, 2) is large enough to ensure those ecosystems can function and evolve without local human-induced disturbances, and 3) is managed to prevent disruptions caused by nearby human activities, including those from local and/or indigenous communities or human visitation.",4,True

:has_definition ""A quality which inheres in a astronomical body or astronomical body part by virtue of the variation in its material composition, participation in geological processes, and the variation in is land- and hydroforms."" .

,Geodiversity is a type of physical object quality defined by the variation in material composition, participation in geological processes, and the variation in its land- and hydroforms. This quality inheres in an astronomical body or an astronomical body part.",2,True

:has_definition ""An IUCN protected area which includes a primarily natural formation designated to be of high natural heritage value and the environmental systems which it determines (e.g. the spray zone of a waterfall monument).""

,An IUCN natural monument or feature is a type of area that is protected according to IUCN guidelines and is defined as an IUCN protected area which includes a primarily natural formation designated to be of high natural heritage value, along with the environmental systems it determines, such as the spray zone of a waterfall monument. This type also overlaps some aspects of a natural monument. Furthermore, it is synonymously related to the term ""natural monument.""",4,True

:has_definition ""An IUCN protected area within which the habitats of or ecosystems used by floral and faunal species deemed to be of international, national, or local importance are maintained, conserved, or restored such that their composition and functional integrity are maintained.""

,An IUCN Habitat Species Management Area is a type of area protected according to IUCN guidelines. It is defined as an IUCN protected area within which the habitats of or ecosystems used by floral and faunal species deemed to be of international, national, or local importance are maintained, conserved, or restored such that their composition and functional integrity are maintained. This area is also broadly referred to as a Habitat Management Area and is relatedly known as a Species Management Area.",4,True

:has_definition ""An ecosystem which has been causally isolated from a larger ecosystem within which it was previously embedded, such that the direct exchange of materials, resources, and energy between these systems is severely or entirely curtailed."" .

,An ecosystem fragment is a type of ecosystem and also a type of entity that is at least formed as a result of some ecosystem fragmentation process. It is defined as an ecosystem which has been causally isolated from a larger ecosystem within which it was previously embedded, such that the direct exchange of materials, resources, and energy between these systems is severely or entirely curtailed.",3,True

:has_definition ""A process during which one or more parts of an ecosystem become causally isolated such that the direct flow or exchange of materials, resources, and energy between a given fragment and the remainder of the original system is severely curtailed or entirely halted."" .

,The ecosystem fragmentation process is equivalent to an intersection involving processes related to ecosystems and those that necessarily involve an ecosystem as an input or result in the creation of an ecosystem fragment. This process is categorized under ecosystem processes, biological processes, and processes that necessarily have an ecosystem as an input or lead to the formation of an ecosystem fragment. Additionally, it's considered a type of process that is causally upstream of or within ecosystem decay. The ecosystem fragmentation process is defined as a process during which one or more parts of an ecosystem become causally isolated, significantly reducing or completely stopping the direct flow or exchange of materials, resources, and energy between a fragment and the rest of the original ecosystem.",7,True

:has_definition ""A protected area in which management objectives have been declared, by a local governing body or authority, to adhere to the guidelines set forth by the International Union for the Conservation of Nature (IUCN)."" .

,An area protected according to IUCN guidelines is a type of area of protected biodiversity and is also known as an IUCN protected area. It is defined as a protected area in which management objectives have been declared by a local governing body or authority to adhere to the guidelines set forth by the International Union for the Conservation of Nature (IUCN).,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001170,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A process during which an ecosystem, its parts, or the processes it participates in are modified by human intervention to accomplish an objective.""

,An active ecosystem management process is a type of anthropogenic modulatory intervention process, as well as a type of anthropogenic environmental process. It is described as a process that involves the modification of an ecosystem, its components, or the processes it participates in through human intervention to achieve a specific goal. This type of process is also characterized as something that necessitates the participation of at least one ecosystem. The term ""active ecosystem management process"" is exactly synonymous with ""ecosystem management"" and has related synonyms including ""Umweltmaßnahme"" and ""environmental management.""",7,True
:has_definition ""An active management process which has the conservation of an ecosystem, or a part thereof, as its primary objective.""

,A conservation-focused active ecosystem management process is a specific type of active ecosystem management process. It is defined as an active management process that primarily aims at the conservation of an ecosystem, or a part of it. Furthermore, this process is related to several synonyms, including Umweltschutz, conservation action, conservation process, and nature conservation.",6,True

:has_definition ""An IUCN protected area which 1) includes entities that have been deemed to be of high scenic quality, 2) is composed of a historically stable assemblage of causally interlinked natural and anthropised ecosystems that provides cultural ecosystem services, and 3) hosts traditional and sustainable human activities."" .

,An IUCN protected landscape/seascape is a type of area protected according to IUCN guidelines. It is defined as an IUCN protected area that includes entities deemed to be of high scenic quality. It is composed of a historically stable assemblage of causally interlinked natural and anthropised ecosystems that provide cultural ecosystem services. Additionally, it hosts traditional and sustainable human activities.",2,True
:has_definition ""A site which is bounded or relativised by a material entity which is of spiritual significance to one or more human groups."" .

,A sacred site is a type of site that is defined as a site which is bounded or relativized by a material entity of spiritual significance to one or more human groups.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001174,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

:has_definition ""A process during which an ecosystem fragment loses its system integrity, with many of its resident ecological populations 1) losing their habitats, 2) undergoing a loss of functional and phylogenetic diversity, and 3) undergoing a subsequent genetic destabilisation through inbreeding."" .

,Ecosystem decay is a type of ecosystem process that involves several participants, including habitats, ecosystem fragments, and ecological communities. It is also causally downstream of or within some ecosystem fragmentation process. Ecosystem decay is defined as a process during which an ecosystem fragment loses its system integrity. This loss of integrity leads to multiple adverse outcomes for the resident ecological populations. These outcomes include the loss of habitats, a reduction in both functional and phylogenetic diversity, and a subsequent genetic destabilization through inbreeding.",6,True
:has_definition ""An ecosystem fragmentation process during which discontinuities emerge in the habitats of one or more ecological populations."" .

,The habitat fragmentation process, which is a specific form of ecosystem fragmentation process, is defined as an ecosystem fragmentation process during which discontinuities emerge in the habitats of one or more ecological populations.",2,True

:has_definition ""An environment which has its properties and composition largely determined by the presence of a metazoan which lacks a vetebral column and which has a habitat that is found in an aquatic environmental system."" .

,The environment associated with an aquatic invertebrate is characterized by its similarity to an ecosystem determined by metazoans that are not vertebrates and have habitats overlapping with aquatic environments. This environment is a type of animal-associated environment, specifically defined by its properties and composition being largely determined by the presence of metazoans lacking a vertebral column and with habitats in aquatic environmental systems.",4,True
:has_definition ""Land which is regularly manipulated by human activities, such as plowing or tilling, in order to grow crops."" .

,Arable land is a type of land that is defined as land which is regularly manipulated by human activities, such as plowing or tilling, in order to grow crops. This kind of land is also characterized as something that at least has some arable quality.",3,True
:has_definition ""Land which hosts a community of herbaceous plants - such as grasses and forbs - upon which animals may graze."" .
,Pasturable land is a type of land defined as land which hosts a community of herbaceous plants, such as grasses and forbs, upon which animals may graze.",2,True
:has_definition ""An environmental system determined by a cnidarian or part of a cnidarian."" .

,The environment associated with cnidarians is the same as an environment that intersects with both an animal-associated environment and an environment at least determined by a union of cnidaria and something that is at least part of some cnidaria. This cnidarian-associated environment is a specific type of animal-associated environment and also a type of environment that is at least determined by a union of cnidaria and something that is at least part of some cnidaria. Furthermore, the cnidarian-associated environment is defined as an environmental system determined by a cnidarian or part of a cnidarian.",4,True
:has_definition ""An environment which has its properties and composition determined by a portion of Bondon cheese."" .
,The Bondon cheese environment is a type of environmental system, defined as an environment whose properties and composition are determined by a portion of Bondon cheese.",2,True
:has_definition ""A surface layer which is composed of the external surface of a root, together with closely adhering soil particles and debris"" .

,The rhizoplane is a type of solid surface layer primarily composed of plant matter, and it is located in the rhizosphere. It is defined as a surface layer composed of the external surface of a root, together with closely adhering soil particles and debris.",4,True
:has_definition ""Pasturable land which is maintained by human activities in order to provide grazing oppoturnities for livestock."" .
,Tended pasturable land is a specific type of pasturable land, defined as pasturable land that is maintained through human activities to provide grazing opportunities for livestock.",2,True

:has_definition ""Land which either hosts plant communities upon which animals may graze has been manipulated by tilling, ploughing, or other human activity for the purposes of seed sowing or planting crops."" .

,Arable or pasturable land is defined as land that either hosts plant communities upon which animals may graze or has been manipulated by tilling, ploughing, or other human activities for the purposes of seed sowing or planting crops. This type of land is essentially the same as the intersection of land and something that at least has part of the union of arable land and pasturable land. Additionally, arable or pasturable land is a type of land and also a type of something that at least has part of the union of arable land and pasturable land.",4,True
:has_definition ""A quality inhereing in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being periodically and mechanically manipulated to loosen and mix any soil which it has as a part."" .

,Arable is a type of environmental condition defined by a quality inherent in a bearer due to the bearer being periodically and mechanically manipulated to loosen and mix any soil which it possesses.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001185,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

:has_definition ""Soil which has increased levels of molecules or ions capable of donating a hydron (proton or hydrogen ion) to other chemical entities, or, alternatively, capable of forming covalent bonds with other chemicals via the acceptance of an electron pair, resulting in a bulk pH measurement of less than 7."" .

,Acidic soil is defined as soil which has increased levels of molecules or ions capable of donating a hydron (proton or hydrogen ion) to other chemical entities, or alternatively, capable of forming covalent bonds with other chemicals via the acceptance of an electron pair, resulting in a bulk pH measurement of less than 7. This definition aligns with the fact that acidic soil is the same as something that intersects with soil and something that at least has the quality of being somewhat acidic. Furthermore, acidic soil is a type of soil and also a type of substance that at least has some acidic quality.",4,True

:has_definition ""Volcanic ash which has increased levels of molecules or ions capable of donating a hydron (proton or hydrogen ion) to other chemical entities, or, alternatively, capable of forming covalent bonds with other chemicals via the acceptance of an electron pair, resulting in a bulk pH measurement of less than 7."" .

,Acidic volcanic ash is defined as volcanic ash that has increased levels of molecules or ions capable of donating a hydron (proton or hydrogen ion) to other chemical entities, or, alternatively, capable of forming covalent bonds with other chemicals via the acceptance of an electron pair, resulting in a bulk pH measurement of less than 7. This definition establishes acidic volcanic ash as being the same as something that intersects the qualities of being volcanic ash and having at least some acidic quality. Furthermore, acidic volcanic ash is categorized as a type of volcanic ash, as well as a type of entity that possesses at least some acidic quality.",4,True
:has_definition ""A digestive tract environment which has its properties and dynamics determined by the digestive tract of an echinoderm from the class Holothuroidea.""

,The holothurian digestive tract is a specific type of environment associated with an animal part or small animal, notably characterized as a type of digestive tract. It is part of at least some organisms from the class Holothuroidea. The definition of the holothurian digestive tract emphasizes that it is a digestive tract environment with unique properties and dynamics determined by the digestive tract of an echinoderm belonging to the Holothuroidea class. Furthermore, the holothurian digestive tract is broadly synonymous with the sea cucumber gut and has an exact synonym, the sea cucumber digestive tract.",6,True
:has_definition ""A bodily fluid which is present in the digestive tract of a member of the Holothuroidea."" .

,The contents of a holothurian digestive tract are defined as a bodily fluid that is present in the digestive tract of a member of the Holothuroidea. This content is both a type of bodily fluid and a type of substance that is located in the holothurian digestive tract. Furthermore, it shares the same characteristics as a substance that intersects with bodily fluids and substances located in the holothurian digestive tract.",4,True

,algal material is a type of organic material.,1,False
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001190,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

:has_definition ""Sea ice which has a brown colouration, either due to 1) the presence of pigments which are or were contained in the members of ecological assemblages, such as algal communities, living or trapped within the ice or 2) due to the presence of trapped sediments.""

,Brown sea ice is synonymous with brownish-colored sea ice and is defined as sea ice which possesses a brown coloration. This coloration can occur for one of two reasons: either through the presence of pigments contained in or previously part of ecological assemblages, such as algal communities living or trapped within the ice, or due to trapped sediments. It is a specific type of sea ice and also falls under the broader category of entities that have some brown quality. Additionally, brown sea ice is equivalent to the intersection of entities that are sea ice and those that have at least some brown quality.",5,True
:has_definition ""The surface layer of a volume of water.""

,The water surface is equivalent to something that intersects with both the liquid surface layer and something that is at least part of some liquid water. It is categorized as a type of aquatic layer, a type of liquid surface layer, and also as a type of something that constitutes at least part of some liquid water. The water surface is defined as the surface layer of a volume of water. Moreover, it has exact synonyms, including ""surface of a body of water"" and ""water body surface.""",7,True
:has_definition ""The surface layer of a mass of sediment.""

,The sediment surface is the same as something that intersects the surface layer and something that is at least part of some sediment. It is a type of surface layer and also a type of something that is at least part of some sediment. The sediment surface is defined as the surface layer of a mass of sediment and has exact synonyms including ""surface of a sedimentary mass"" and ""surface sediment.""",6,True
:has_related_synonym ""A liquid planetary surface which is composed primarily of water."" .

,A water-based planetary surface is synonymous with a liquid planetary surface that is composed primarily of water, and it is defined as the intersection of a liquid planetary surface and a surface that is at least composed primarily of some liquid water. Furthermore, a water-based planetary surface is categorized under various types: it is a type of aquatic layer, a type of liquid planetary surface, a type of liquid surface layer, and a type of surface that at least has a part which intersects with a water surface and is adjacent to something that encompasses both the atmosphere and outer space.",6,True
:has_definition ""A site in which charged particles are influenced by an astronomical body's magnetic field."" .

,A magnetosphere is a type of environmental zone characterized by its ability to shield against cosmic rays and contains an astronomical body. It also overlaps with outer space. Moreover, it is defined as a site in which charged particles are influenced by an astronomical body's magnetic field.",5,True
:has_definition ""An environmental disposition which inheres in an entity that intercepts, attenuates, or blocks radiation."" .

,Radiation shielding disposition is a type of environmental disposition and is defined as an environmental disposition which inheres in an entity that intercepts, attenuates, or blocks radiation.",2,True
:has_definition ""A radiation shielding disposition which inheres in a material or immaterial entity which attenuates or blocks cosmic rays."" .

,Cosmic ray shielding disposition is a type of radiation shielding disposition with a definition as a radiation shielding disposition that inheres in a material or immaterial entity which attenuates or blocks cosmic rays.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001197,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:has_definition ""A magnetosphere which either 1) cannot withstand the pressure of the stellar wind interacting with it, thus allowing the stellar wind to interact with the ionosphere, atmosphere, or surface of the planet generating it or 2) is formed by the interaction of the stellar wind with an astronomical body unshielded by its own magnetosphere."" .

,An induced magnetosphere is a type of magnetosphere defined as a magnetosphere that either cannot withstand the pressure of the stellar wind interacting with it, allowing the stellar wind to interact with the ionosphere, atmosphere, or surface of the planet generating it, or is formed by the interaction of the stellar wind with an astronomical body unshielded by its own magnetosphere.",2,True
:has_definition ""A magnetosphere which shields the body generating it from the stellar wind by withstanding the stellar wind's pressure before it reaches the body."" .

,An intrinsic magnetosphere is a type of magnetosphere that acts as a shield for the body generating it from the stellar wind by withstanding the stellar wind's pressure before it reaches the body.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001199,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An environmental zone which is bounded by material parts of a land mass or the atmosphere or space adjacent to it."" .

,A terrestrial environmental zone is defined as an environmental zone, which is bounded by material parts of a land mass or the atmosphere or space adjacent to it. It is a type of environmental zone that intersects with another environmental zone and is at least part of some planetary landmass. Furthermore, a terrestrial environmental zone is also considered a type of entity that is at least part of some terrestrial biome and is a type of entity that is at least part of some planetary landmass.",5,True
:has_definition ""A terrestrial zone which is bounded by constructed, manufactured, or other anthropogenic material entities."" .

,An anthropised terrestrial environmental zone is defined as a terrestrial zone that is bounded by constructed, manufactured, or other anthropogenic material entities. It is identified as being the same as the intersection of a terrestrial environmental zone and at least part of some anthropogenic terrestrial biome. Furthermore, an anthropised terrestrial environmental zone is classified as a type of terrestrial environmental zone as well as a type of entity that is at least part of some anthropogenic terrestrial biome.",4,True
:has_definition ""An environmental zone which is bounded by material parts of a marine environment."" .

,A Marine Environmental Zone is identical to an entity that emerges from the intersection of an Environmental Zone and an entity that is, at least in part, part of a marine environment. It is categorized as a subtype of both Environmental Zones and entities that constitute, at least partially, a marine environment. Furthermore, a Marine Environmental Zone is defined as an Environmental Zone that is demarcated by the material aspects of a marine environment.",4,True
:has_definition ""Soil or sediment which has been eroded and influenced by flowing water and redeposited in a non-marine setting."" .

,Alluvium is a type of environmental material characterized by being porous and granular. It is primarily composed of a union of alluvial soil and alluvial sediment. The definition of alluvium is soil or sediment that has been eroded and influenced by flowing water and redeposited in a non-marine setting.,5,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001203,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""Sediment which has been transported by flowing water and redeposited in a non-marine setting."" .

,Alluvial sediment is a type of sediment defined as sediment which has been transported by flowing water and redeposited in a non-marine setting.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001204,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A rock which is formed as a result of the lithification of alluvium."" .

,Alluvial deposit is a type of rock that is formed as a result of lithification, a process that turns loose material into solid rock. It is primarily composed of materials that are a combination of alluvial soil and alluvial sediment. Additionally, alluvial deposit is defined as a rock which results from the lithification of alluvium.",4,True
:has_definition ""A process during which sediments compact under pressure, expel connate fluids, and gradually become solid sedimentary rock."" .

,Lithification is the same as an intersection involving a material transformation process and a process that at least has sediment as its input, and results in the formation of sedimentary rock. It is classified as a type of material transformation process and also considered a type of biological process. Furthermore, lithification is characterized as a process that necessarily involves sediment as its input and leads to the formation of sedimentary rock. The definition of lithification is a process during which sediments compact under pressure, expel connate fluids, and gradually become solid sedimentary rock.",6,True
:has_definition ""An ecosystem in which grasses (Graminae) are the dominant form of vegetation and determine the system's structure and dynamics.""^^xsd:string

,The grassland ecosystem is a type of terrestrial ecosystem defined as an ecosystem where grasses (Graminae) are the dominant form of vegetation, determining the system's structure and dynamics. It has the exact synonyms ""GRASSLAND"" and ""grassland."" Additionally, it has related synonyms including ""Grassland,"" ""down,"" ""downland,"" ""downs,"" ""glade,"" ""grazing area,"" and ""herbaceous area.""",11,True
:has_definition ""An area of land used for the herding and grazing of livestock.""^^xsd:string

,A ranch is a type of farm and also a type of entity that is at least part of some rangeland biome. It is defined as an area of land used for the herding and grazing of livestock. Additionally, ""ranch"" is a synonym related to itself.",4,True
:has_definition ""An area of wetland which overlaps a swamp ecosystem.""^^xsd:string .

,A swamp area is a type of wetland area and it is also a type of something that at least overlaps some swamp ecosystem. Furthermore, a swamp area is defined as an area of wetland which overlaps a swamp ecosystem.",3,True

:has_definition ""A terrestrial ecosystem which is inundated or saturated by surface or ground water at a frequency and duration sufficient to support, and that under normal circumstances does support, a prevalence of vegetation typically adapted for life in saturated soil conditions.""^^xsd:string

,The wetland ecosystem is recognized as a type of ecosystem and is characterized by being a part of the intersection between planetary landmasses and components primarily comprised of soil and wet qualities. It is defined as a terrestrial ecosystem which is inundated or saturated by surface or ground water at a frequency and duration sufficient to support, and under normal circumstances does support, a prevalence of vegetation typically adapted for life in saturated soil conditions. The wetland ecosystem is exactly synonymous with both ""WETLAND"" and ""Wetland.""

Furthermore, it has a variety of narrow synonyms that include EstuarineWetland, LacustrineWetland, MarineWetland, PalustrineWetland, RiparianWetland, TerrestrialWetland, back marsh, backswamp, backwater, barrier flat, blanket bog, bog, cienaga, dismal, everglade, floating marsh, forested wetland, marsh, mire, mud flat, peat cutting area, peatland, quagmire, quaking bog, riparian area, slash, slough, slue, swamp forest, and tulelands. Additionally, it has related synonyms which are moor, morass, and muskeg, further broadening the terminology associated with wetland ecosystems.",38,True
:has_definition ""A planned process during which an environmental system is modified to mitigate or nullify the impacts of flooding.""

,Defence against flooding is the same as something that falls at the intersection of an anthropogenic modulatory intervention process and something that at least negatively regulates some flooding. It is both a type of anthropogenic modulatory intervention process and a type that negatively regulates flooding. The definition of defence against flooding is a planned process during which an environmental system is modified to mitigate or nullify the impacts of flooding. In terms of terminology, ""defence against flooding"" has the exact synonym ""defense against flooding."" Additionally, it has several related synonyms including ""defence against floods,"" ""defense against floods,"" ""flood defence,"" ""flood defence intervention,"" ""flood defense,"" and ""flood defense intervention.""",11,True
:has_definition ""An electromagnetic radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta are emitted from a star.""

,Stellar radiation, which is a type of electromagnetic radiation and also a type of process that has some star as its causal agent, is defined as an electromagnetic radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta are emitted from a star. It is the same as the intersection of electromagnetic radiation and a process that has a star as its causal agent. Furthermore, stellar radiation has a narrow synonym: solar radiation.",5,True

:has_definition ""A stellar radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta are emitted from a star at wavelengths and frequencies which travel exclusively in a line-of-sight fashion and which may produce molecular rotation and torsion on contact with matter.""

,Microwave stellar radiation, which is both a type of stellar radiation and a type of microwave radiation, is equivalent to an intersection involving microwave radiation and a process with a causal agent being some star. It is defined as a stellar radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta, emitted from a star at specific wavelengths and frequencies, travel exclusively in a line-of-sight manner and may induce molecular rotation and torsion upon interacting with matter. Additionally, microwave stellar radiation is closely related to, and has a narrow synonym, microwave solar radiation.",5,True
:has_definition ""A stellar radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta are emitted from a star at wavelengths ranging from millimetre to kilometer scales.""

,Radio wave stellar radiation is identified as an intersection between something that involves radio wave radiation and something that processes with a star as a causal agent. It is both a type of stellar radiation and a type of radio wave radiation. The definition of radio wave stellar radiation is a stellar radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta are emitted from a star at wavelengths ranging from millimeter to kilometer scales. Additionally, radio wave stellar radiation is narrowly synonymous with radio wave solar radiation.",5,True

:has_definition ""A stellar radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta are emitted from a star when molecules change their rotational-vibrational movements, usually at wavelengths between 760 nm and 1 mm.""

,Infrared stellar radiation is a type of stellar radiation as well as a type of infrared radiation. It is defined as a stellar radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta are emitted from a star when molecules change their rotational-vibrational movements, usually at wavelengths between 760 nm and 1 mm. This specific type of radiation is synonymous with infrared radiation broadly, infra-red stellar radiation exactly, and has a more narrowly defined synonym as infrared solar radiation. Additionally, it is relatedly known as IR stellar radiation. Furthermore, infrared stellar radiation is the same as something that is at the intersection of something that involves infrared radiation and something that involves a process with a causal agent being some star.",8,True
:has_definition ""A stellar radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta are emitted from a star at wavelengths between 380 nm and 760 nm.""

,Visible spectrum stellar radiation is defined as a process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta are emitted from a star at wavelengths between 380 nm and 760 nm. It is a type of stellar radiation and also a type of visible spectrum radiation, sharing the same characteristics as the intersection of radiation within the visible spectrum and processes that have a star as their causal agent. Additionally, visible spectrum stellar radiation is exactly synonymous with optical stellar radiation and has a narrow synonym, visible spectrum solar radiation.",6,True
:has_definition ""A stellar radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta are emitted from a star at wavelengths between 10 nm and 400 nm.""

,Ultraviolet stellar radiation is the same as something that both involves ultraviolet radiation and has at least one process that is caused by a star. It is a type of stellar radiation as well as a type of ultraviolet radiation. Ultraviolet stellar radiation is defined as a stellar radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta are emitted from a star at wavelengths between 10 nm and 400 nm. Additionally, ultraviolet stellar radiation is narrowly synonymous with ultraviolet solar radiation.",5,True
:has_definition ""A stellar radiation process during which penetrating electromagnetic radiation is emitted by high-energy electrons as they fall into a lower state of energy.""

,X-ray stellar radiation is the same as something that is at the intersection of something that has X-ray radiation and something that at least has a process with a causal agent being some star. It is a type of ionizing stellar radiation and also a type of X-ray radiation. X-ray stellar radiation is defined as a stellar radiation process during which penetrating electromagnetic radiation is emitted by high-energy electrons as they fall into a lower state of energy. It has an exact synonym, ""X-ray stellar radiation,"" and a narrow synonym, ""X-ray solar radiation.""",6,True
:has_definition ""A stellar radiation process during which penetrating electromagnetic radiation is emitted from the radioactive decay (gamma decay) of atomic nuclei.""

,Gamma ray stellar radiation is the same as an intersection of gamma ray radiation and a process that has a causal agent being some star. It is a type of ionizing stellar radiation and also a type of gamma ray radiation. The definition of gamma ray stellar radiation is a stellar radiation process during which penetrating electromagnetic radiation is emitted from the radioactive decay (gamma decay) of atomic nuclei. Additionally, gamma ray stellar radiation has a narrow synonym: gamma-ray solar radiation.",5,True

:has_definition ""A stellar radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta are emitted from a star with sufficient energy to disrupt molecular bonds or alter the electron number of atoms.""

,Ionizing stellar radiation, also known as ionising stellar radiation, is a specific type of stellar radiation and a kind of ionizing radiation. It can be defined as a stellar radiation process during which electromagnetic waves or their quanta, emitted from a star, possess enough energy to disrupt molecular bonds or alter the electron number of atoms. This radiation is equivalent to the intersection of ionizing radiation and processes that have a star as their causal agent. Additionally, ionizing stellar radiation has a narrow synonym: ionising solar radiation.",6,True
:has_definition ""A process during which liquid water accumulates in a site, most often in some form of container."" .

,The water accumulation process is a type of liquid accumulation process and is also considered a type of hydrological process. It is characterized as a process that necessarily involves liquid water as a participant and results in the formation of some water body as its output. Furthermore, it is defined as a process during which liquid water accumulates in a site, most often in some form of container.",5,True
:has_definition ""A commercial building which contains parts used as workplaces primarily for administrative and managerial workers."" .

,Office buildings are a type of commercial building and are defined as commercial buildings which contain parts used as workplaces primarily for administrative and managerial workers. Additionally, they are characterized by having at least some office parts and some toilet fixtures as part of their structure.",4,True
:has_definition ""A building which is primarily used to facilitate the buying or selling of goods or services."" .

,A commercial building is defined as a building which is primarily used to facilitate the buying or selling of goods or services. It is a type of building that intersects with buildings that at least participate in some usage of an environment for business. Furthermore, a commercial building is categorized as a type of entity that at least participates in some usage of an environment for business.",4,True
:has_definition ""A process during which wood is processed into beams or planks.""

,The lumber production process is a type of planetary manufacturing process defined as a process during which wood is processed into beams or planks. This process is also exactly synonymous with lumber production, timber production, and timber production process.",5,True
:has_definition ""A building part within which administrative work is done by an organisations users in order to support and realise the objectives of that organization."" .

,An office is a type of building part and it is defined as a building part within which administrative work is done by an organization's users in order to support and realize the objectives of that organization.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001225,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_broad_synonym ""protected area with sustainable use of natural resources""

:has_definition ""An IUCN protected area within which 1) natural ecosystems and their resources are either conserved or used through non-industrial human activities, 2) usage activites contribute to conservation goals, ensuring inter-generational security for local communities' livelihoods, and 3) the majority of benefits derived from the use of ecosystems are received by communities living near or in the area."" .

,An IUCN protected area with sustainable use of natural resources is defined as a type of area protected according to IUCN guidelines, which at least overlaps with an intersection of the planetary surface and an environment primarily composed of natural elements. This type of protected area is characterized by the conservation or sustainable use of natural ecosystems and their resources through non-industrial human activities. These usage activities contribute to conservation goals, ensuring inter-generational security for local communities' livelihoods, with the majority of benefits derived from the use of ecosystems being received by communities living near or in the area. It is also broadly referred to as a protected area with sustainable use of natural resources.",4,True
:has_definition ""A natural environment which is located on a land mass."" .

,The terrestrial natural environment is defined as a natural environment located on a landmass, which is a type of natural environment and also a type that includes at least part of a planetary landmass. It is synonymous with the intersection of natural environments and those that are part of a planetary landmass.",4,True
:has_definition ""A natural environment which is within a water body."" .

,An aquatic natural environment is defined as a natural environment within a water body. It is a type of natural environment that intersects with entities that are at least partly part of some water body. Thus, the aquatic natural environment is both a category of natural environments and entities that are associated with water bodies.",4,True
:has_definition ""A site in which the attraction of satellites by gravitation is dominated by an astronomical body, bounded by a zero-velocity surface.""

,The Hill sphere is a type of environmental zone that intersects with entities processing some gravitational motion and having a causal agent, which is an astronomical body. It is also defined as a site where the attraction of satellites by gravitation is dominated by an astronomical body, bounded by a zero-velocity surface. Furthermore, the Hill sphere contains at least one astronomical body and is exactly synonymous with the Roche sphere.",5,True

:has_definition ""A site in which the combined gravitational pull of the two large astronomical bodies is such that a smaller body, affected only by gravity, can maintain a stable position relative to those two large bodies and orbit with them due to centripetal force.""

,A Lagrangian point is a type of environmental zone that partially overlaps with or includes at least some aspects of a Hill sphere and is characterized by having at least two components of a Hill sphere. It is defined as a site where the combined gravitational forces of two large astronomical bodies create a scenario where a smaller body, influenced solely by gravity, can maintain a stable position relative to the two larger bodies and orbit along with them, courtesy of centripetal force. This concept is also exactly synonymous with L-points, Lagrange points, and libration points.",7,True
:has_definition ""A marginal sea biome which is located in a region with a tropical climate."" .

,The tropical marginal sea biome is a type of marginal sea biome and also falls under the category of tropical biomes. It is defined as a marginal sea biome that is situated in a region characterized by a tropical climate.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001231,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""Organic material which is in a solid phase and contained in sedimentary rock."" .

,Kerogen is a type of organic and solid environmental material that is at least partially surrounded by some sedimentary rock. It is defined as organic material which is in a solid phase and contained in sedimentary rock.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001232,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

:has_definition ""Kerogen which cotains alginite, amorphous organic matter, cyanobacteria, freshwater algae, and land plant resins, thus having a hydrogen to carbon ratio above 1.25, and oxygen to carbon ratio below 0.15, readily produces liquid hydrocarbons, has reduced concentrations of aromatic structures, and primarily derived from proteins and lipids."" .

,Sapropelic kerogen is a type of kerogen that is defined as containing alginite, amorphous organic matter, cyanobacteria, freshwater algae, and land plant resins. It has a hydrogen to carbon ratio above 1.25 and an oxygen to carbon ratio below 0.15. This type of kerogen readily produces liquid hydrocarbons, has reduced concentrations of aromatic structures, and is primarily derived from proteins and lipids. Additionally, sapropelic kerogen is a type of substance that derives into hydrocarbons that have at least some qualities of a liquid.",3,True
:has_definition ""Kerogen from which heavy hydrocarbons (such as oils) are derived following chemical break down."" .

,Labile kerogen, which is a type of kerogen, is defined as kerogen from which heavy hydrocarbons, such as oils, are derived following chemical breakdown. Additionally, labile kerogen is a type of substance that at least derives into some petroleum.",3,True
:has_definition ""Kerogen from which light hydrocarbons (such as hydrocarbon gases) are derived following chemical break down."" .

,Recalcitrant kerogen is a type of kerogen that is defined as kerogen from which light hydrocarbons, such as hydrocarbon gases, are derived following chemical breakdown. This indicates that recalcitrant kerogen is a type of substance that, at the very least, derives into some hydrocarbon gas.",3,True

:has_definition ""Kerogen which is enriched in sulfur compounds, has a hydrogen to carbon ratio under 1.25, an oxygen to carbon ratio between 0.03 and 0.18, derives into mixtures of hydrocarbon gas and oil, and derives from marine organic materials (primarily lipids) which are formed in reducing environments."" .

,Planktonic kerogen is a specific type of kerogen that is characterized by its derivation from planktonic material, indicating its origin from marine organic materials, primarily lipids, formed in reducing environments. This type of kerogen is noted for its transformation into substances that are part of the intersection of petroleum and hydrocarbon gas. Additionally, planktonic kerogen is distinguished by its elevated levels of sulfur molecular entities. It is defined by its enrichment in sulfur compounds, possessing a hydrogen to carbon ratio below 1.25 and an oxygen to carbon ratio that ranges from 0.03 to 0.18. This kerogen evolves into mixtures of hydrocarbon gas and oil, underlying its significant role in the geochemical processes leading to hydrocarbon formation.",5,True
:has_definition ""Planktonic kerogen which has high concentrations of sulfur compounds."" .
,Sulfrous kerogen, which is a type of planktonic kerogen, is defined as planktonic kerogen that has high concentrations of sulfur compounds.",2,True

:has_definition ""Kerogen which derives from land plants, resembles wood or coral in structure, has a hydrogen to carbon ratio under 1, an oxygen to carbon ratio between 0.03 to 0.3, and which primarily produces coal or hydrocarbon gas on degradation."" .

,Humic kerogen is a type of kerogen that at least derives from some viridiplantae and also transforms into a substance that is a union of hydrocarbon gas and coal. It is defined as kerogen originating from land plants, resembling wood or coral in structure, with a hydrogen to carbon ratio under 1, an oxygen to carbon ratio between 0.03 to 0.3, and primarily produces coal or hydrocarbon gas upon degradation.",4,True
:has_definition ""Kerogen which has a hydrogen to carbon ratio less than  0.5 and primarily composed of polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons."" .

,Residual kerogen is a type of kerogen and is categorized as a hydrocarbon-based environmental material. It is characterized by being at least composed primarily of polycyclic hydrocarbons. Furthermore, residual kerogen is defined as kerogen which has a hydrogen to carbon ratio less than 0.5 and is primarily composed of polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons.",4,True

,The forest canopy is a type of canopy and is considered a part of some forest ecosystems.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001240,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A canopy which is part of a woodland ecosystem."" .
,A woodland canopy is defined as a canopy that is part of a woodland ecosystem, which is a type of canopy. It is also identified as part of some woodland ecosystem.",3,True
:has_definition ""A canopy which is composed of the aboveground portion, or crowns, of a community of crop plants."" .
,A crop canopy is a type of canopy and is part of at least some cropland ecosystem. It is defined as a canopy composed of the aboveground portion, or crowns, of a community of crop plants.",3,True
:has_definition ""A vegetation layer which is formed by a collection of individual plant crowns, themselves constituting part of the aboveground portion of a plant community."" .

,Canopy is a type of vegetation layer, defined as a vegetation layer formed by a collection of individual plant crowns, which themselves constitute part of the aboveground portion of a plant community.",2,True

:has_definition ""An ecosystem which is determined by communities of plants with a tree growth form and in which members of those communities form continuous or discontinuous regions of canopy cover."" .

,A forest ecosystem is a type of terrestrial ecosystem and also a type of entity that at least has part some forest canopy. It is defined as an ecosystem which is determined by communities of plants with a tree growth form and in which members of those communities form continuous or discontinuous regions of canopy cover.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001244,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:has_definition ""An ecosystem which 1) is determined by communities of annual crops, perennial woody crops, or by actively tilled land, 2) is primarily used for agricultural activity, and 3) contains no village or larger human settlement."" .

,The cropland ecosystem is a type of terrestrial ecosystem defined as an ecosystem which 1) is determined by communities of annual crops, perennial woody crops, or by actively tilled land, 2) is primarily used for agricultural activity, and 3) contains no village or larger human settlement.",2,True

:has_definition ""An ecosystem which is determined by communities of plants with a tree growth form and in which members of those communities are spaced sufficiently far apart to allow sunlight to illuminate the understory."" .

,A woodland ecosystem is a type of terrestrial ecosystem and also a type of entity that includes at least a part of some woodland canopy. It is defined as an ecosystem characterized by communities of plants with a tree growth form, where the members of these communities are spaced sufficiently apart to allow sunlight to illuminate the understory.",3,True
:has_definition ""A process during which humans rear animals or plants on land for harvest and consumption.""

,The agricultural process is equivalent to an intersection of environmental system processes and processes that occur in the union of cropland, village, and rangeland biomes. It is classified as a type of anthropogenic environmental process and occurs in planetary landmasses, specifically within the union of cropland, village, and rangeland biomes. The agricultural process is defined as a process during which humans rear animals or plants on land for harvest and consumption, and it is synonymously related to agriculture.",6,True
:has_definition ""An agricultural process during which humans rear plants on land for harvest and consumption.""

,An agronomic process is a type of agricultural process that involves humans rearing plants on land for harvest and consumption. It specifically has at least some viridiplantae (green plants) as participants. Additionally, agronomy is a related synonym for an agronomic process.",4,True
:has_definition ""An agricultural process during which humans rear animals on land for harvest and consumption.""

,Animal husbandry is a type of agricultural process and is also related to agriculture as a synonym. It is a type of process that involves at least some metazoans as participants. Animal husbandry is defined as an agricultural process during which humans rear animals on land for harvest and consumption.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001249,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An aquaculture process during which humans rear crustaceans.""

,The crustacean farming process, also known as crustacean aquaculture and related to the aquaculture of crustaceans, is a type of animal aquaculture process. It is defined as an aquaculture process during which humans rear crustaceans.",4,True
:has_definition ""An aquaculture process during which humans rear finfish.""

,The finfish farming process is a type of animal aquaculture process and is defined as an aquaculture process during which humans rear finfish. It is exactly synonymous with finfish aquaculture and is relatedly synonymous with the aquaculture of finfish.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001251,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An aquaculture process during which humans rear molluscs.""

,The mollusc farming process, which is a type of animal aquaculture process, is defined as an aquaculture process during which humans rear molluscs. It has the exact synonym ""mollusc aquaculture"" and is also relatedly referred to as the ""aquaculture of molluscs.""",4,True
:has_definition ""An aquaculture process during which humans rear seaweed.""

,Seaweed farming process, also known as seaweed aquaculture and relatedly referred to as aquaculture of seaweed, is a type of plant aquaculture process. It is defined as an aquaculture process during which humans rear seaweed.",4,True
:has_definition ""An aquaculture process during which humans rear freshwater macrophytes.""

,The freshwater macrophyte farming process is a type of plant aquaculture process, defined as an aquaculture process during which humans rear freshwater macrophytes. This process is exactly synonymous with freshwater macrophyte aquaculture and is also relatedly known as the aquaculture of freshwater macrophytes.",4,True
:has_definition ""An aquaculture process during which humans rear animals.""

,The animal aquaculture process is a type of aquaculture process and is also a type of process that involves at least some metazoa as participants. It is defined as an aquaculture process during which humans rear animals. Moreover, the animal aquaculture process has the exact synonym ""animal aquaculture"" and a related synonym ""aquaculture of animals.""",5,True
:has_definition ""An aquaculture process during which humans rear plants.""

,The plant aquaculture process is a type of aquaculture process that involves participants such as viridiplantae. It is defined as an aquaculture process during which humans rear plants. Moreover, ""plant aquaculture"" is an exact synonym for the plant aquaculture process, and ""aquaculture of plants"" is considered a related synonym.",5,True
:has_definition ""A shrimp pond which is embedded in a coastal water body."" .

,A coastal shrimp pond is a type of shrimp pond and a type of hydroform. It is also considered a type of entity that is at least partially encompassed by some coastal water body. Moreover, it is defined as a shrimp pond which is embedded in a coastal water body.",4,True
:has_definition ""Saline water which is derived from sea water and used during the cultivation of crustaceans."" .

,Saline shrimp pond water is defined as saline water derived from sea water and used during the cultivation of crustaceans. It is the same as the intersection of saline water and something that is at least part of some shrimp pond. Furthermore, saline shrimp pond water is categorized as a type of saline water, a part of something within a shrimp pond, and something that participates in a crustacean farming process.",6,True

:has_definition ""A fog which is composed of liquid aerosols and gases derived from volcanic gas emissions (primarily sulfur oxides), formed when sulfur-bearing gases react with sunlight, oxygen, and moisture in an atmosphere."" .

,Vog is a type of fog characterized by its unique composition and formation process. It is composed of liquid aerosols and gases that originate from volcanic gas emissions, primarily sulfur oxides. This composition results from the interaction between sulfur molecular entities and substances derived from sulfur oxide, which are outputs of volcanic eruptions. The formation of vog is a consequence of a gas emission process that is part of a volcanic eruption, involving the reaction of sulfur-bearing gases with sunlight, oxygen, and moisture in the atmosphere.",4,True
:has_definition ""A process during which materials deemed to be waste are removed from a site and transported to another site designated for its storage."" .

,The transport of waste to a designated storage site is identified as a type of waste disposal process, which implies an activity that involves at least some area designated for waste storage. This process is defined as an operation during which materials recognized as waste are removed from one site and transported to another site specifically designated for its storage.",3,True
:has_definition ""A process during which materials deemed to be waste are transported away from a site.""

,The waste disposal process is an anthropogenic environmental process and a type of pollution control. It is characterized by involving at least some material transport process and includes the participation of waste material. The process is defined as one during which materials deemed to be waste are transported away from a site. This process is also precisely known by its synonyms in different languages: ""Abfallentsorgungsprozess"" in German, ""proceso de eliminación de residuos"" in Spanish, and ""processo di smaltimento rifiuti"" in Italian.",8,True
:has_definition ""A waste disposal process during which the feces of human children is transported to a designated storage site."" .

,The transport of child feces to a designated site is recognized as a specific type of waste transport to a designated storage site. This process is defined as a waste disposal process during which the feces of human children are transported to a designated storage site, and it is broadly synonymous with child feces disposal. Furthermore, this transport is considered a type of activity that necessarily involves an entity that is both feces and an output of a process which is an intersection of excretion and involves human participants.",4,True
:has_definition ""A process during which materials used in a household and deemed to be waste are removed from the housing unit and transported to another site designated for its storage."" .

,Transport of household waste to a designated storage site is recognized as a form of waste transportation to a specified location for storage. This process involves at least some household waste material and is associated with human residences. It is defined as a procedure where materials that are considered waste in a household are taken out of the dwelling and moved to another location set aside for storing such waste. Additionally, this process is broadly synonymous with household waste disposal.",5,True
:has_definition ""A site which has been designated as a place where humans may defecate."" .

,An area designated for human defecation is a type of environmental zone, which is defined as a site designated as a place where humans may defecate. Additionally, it has the broad synonym ""defecation area.""",3,True
:has_definition ""A site which has been designated for the storage of waste material.""

,An area designated for waste storage is a type of environmental zone, defined as a site which has been designated for the storage of waste material. Additionally, it is related to synonyms such as waste disposal site and waste storage site.",4,True
:has_definition ""An environmental pollution process during which the temperature of an environmental system, or parts thereof, is raised above its natural levels."" .

,Thermal pollution is identified as a category of environmental pollution characterized by its impact on various components, including environmental materials, environmental systems, and astronomical body parts, by either adding or removing elements that result in an alteration of these components. Furthermore, thermal pollution is specifically associated with scenarios where there is an increase in temperature, distinguishing it by its output effect on the union of environmental materials, environmental systems, and astronomical body parts, which also exhibit qualities of elevated temperature. Additionally, thermal pollution is defined as an environmental pollution process that elevates the temperature of an environmental system, or its parts, above their natural levels.",4,True
:has_definition ""A thermal pollution process which occurs in a water body or aquatic environment."" .

,Thermal pollution of an aquatic system is categorized as a type of thermal pollution, hydrological process, and water pollution. It is described as something that at least occurs in some water body or aquatic environment. Additionally, it is defined as a process that intersects with liquid water and involves an increase in temperature. The definition of thermal pollution of an aquatic system is a thermal pollution process which occurs in a water body or aquatic environment.",7,True
:has_definition ""Water which accumulates on a solid surface during precipitation events and snow/ice melt.""

,Stormwater, which is a type of liquid water, is defined as water that accumulates on a solid surface during precipitation events and snow/ice melt. It is also exactly synonymous with storm water.",3,True
:has_definition ""Stormwater which accumulates in an urban ecosystem.""

,Urban stormwater, which has the exact synonym urban storm water, is a type of stormwater specifically associated with urban biomes and areas of developed space. It is defined as stormwater that accumulates in an urban ecosystem.",5,True

:has_definition ""An area of a planet's surface which is primarily covered by constructed or manufactured objects and materials, possibly interspersed with cultivated or anthropically maintained vegetation."" .

,The area of developed space is characterized as a type of anthropised terrestrial environmental zone, and it also falls under the category of something that is, at least in part, part of some urban biome and something that is adjacent to some atmospheric boundary layer. Furthermore, it is defined as an area of a planet's surface which is primarily covered by constructed or manufactured objects and materials, possibly interspersed with cultivated or anthropically maintained vegetation.",4,True
:has_definition ""Stormwater which accumulates in a rural ecosystem.""

,Rural stormwater is a type of stormwater that is specifically located in rural areas, encompassing regions that include a union of cropland, village, and rangeland biomes. It is defined as stormwater which accumulates in a rural ecosystem. Additionally, rural stormwater is exactly synonymous with rural storm water.",5,True
:has_definition ""A surface layer through which liquids or gases cannot pass."" .

,An impermeable surface layer is defined as a surface layer through which liquids or gases cannot pass. It is the same as something that is the intersection of a solid surface layer and something that has at least some impermeable quality. Furthermore, an impermeable surface layer is a type of solid surface layer, and it is also a type of something that has at least some impermeable quality.",4,True
:has_definition ""A construction which comprises a durable surface layer overlying a solid surface intended to sustain vehicular or foot traffic."" .

,Constructed pavement is a type of transport feature and also a type of something that has at least some laminar quality. It is defined as a construction that comprises a durable surface layer overlying a solid surface intended to sustain vehicular or foot traffic.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001273,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A layer which is primarily composed of some liquid material."" .

,The liquid layer is the same as the intersection of the fluid layer and something that is at least composed primarily of some liquid environmental material. It is a type of fluid layer and also a type of something that is at least composed primarily of some liquid environmental material. :has_definition ""A road which is primarily composed of asphalt."" .

:has_definition ""Dust which is primarily composed of slate particles."" .

:has_definition ""A fire which occurs in an industrial area or building."" .

:has_definition ""Dust which is primarily composed of kaolinite particles.""

:has_definition ""A land fire which consumes low-growing plants such as scrub and brush."" .

:has_definition ""A land fire which occurs in a large uncleared or sparsely settled area (as in Australia) usually scrub-covered or forested."" .

:has_definition ""A fire which occurs in a pastureland."" .

:has_definition ""A fire which occurs on land, typically consuming a terrestrial ecosystem as fuel."" .

:has_definition ""A vegetated area which has not been cleared or is sparsely settled, usually scrub-covered or forested""

,A bush area is defined as a vegetated area that has not been cleared or is sparsely settled, usually covered by scrub or forested, and is synonymous with the term ""the bush."" It is specifically the same as an intersection of vegetated areas with areas that at least partially overlap a union of forested areas, scrubland areas, areas of scrub, areas of developed open space, areas of sedge and forb dominated herbaceous vegetation, and areas of gramanoid or herbaceous vegetation. :has_definition ""A an atmospheric storm which originates over tropical or subtropical waters and possesses a warm-core, non-frontal synoptic-scale cyclone with a low pressure centre, spiral rain bands and strong winds."" .

:has_definition ""An atmospheric storm during which a large mass of atmospheric gas rotates around a centre of low atmospheric pressure, generating high winds which spiral towards that centre."" .

It is also characterized as a type of phenomenon that at least has a participant that intersects with an area of low atmospheric pressure and is centered or qualitatively described in a certain way. :has_definition ""A cyclone which rotates around an area low atmospheric pressure with increased temperature.""

:has_definition ""A layer of liquid that is part of an estuary.""^^xsd:string .

:has_definition ""An oasis is a vegetated area located in a desert, supplied with water from a water source which it surrounds, and surrounded by arid soil, sand, or rock.""

This area is also characterized by being at least partially surrounded by arid terrain, which includes a combination of soil, sand, or rock, and may overlap with a spring. Furthermore, an oasis is classified as a type of vegetated area and a type of area that is at least partially encircled by arid land consisting of soil, sand, or rock. :has_definition ""An environment which is determined by a bone element."" .

,The bone element environment is an environment that is characterized by a few key relationships. Firstly, it is equivalent to an environment that represents the intersection between an anatomical entity environment and an environment that is at least determined by some bone element. This environment is categorized as a type of ecosystem, indicating its ecological significance. Additionally, it falls under the category of an anatomical entity environment, highlighting its relevance to biological structures. It is also considered a type of environment that is at least determined by some bone element, which underscores the crucial role bone elements play in defining this environment. The bone element environment is defined as an environment determined by a bone element, further emphasizing the essential influence of bone elements in shaping this particular environment.",5,True
:has_definition ""A liquid astronomical body part which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of liquid water and is held in shape or sustained by an environmental process."" .

This definition encompasses hydroform being the same as the intersection of entities that are at least part of some water body, entities that are composed primarily of liquid water, and entities that contain a process involving water flow. Moreover, hydroform is categorized as a type of entity that is a liquid astronomical body part, part of a water body, contains a water flow process, and is composed primarily of liquid water.",6,True

:has_definition ""A surface layer which is composed primarily of some liquid."" .

:has_definition ""A surface layer which is composed primarily of solid environmental material."" .
