,The ice accumulation process is categorized under several types, including a hydrological process, a material accumulation process, and a specific intersection involving processes that at least partly involve a union of freezing and material transport processes, as well as those that have water ice as at least one participant. Furthermore, the ice accumulation process is defined as a material accumulation process during which ice forms in an environmental material or an existing accumulation of ice increases in mass.",4,True
:has_definition ""A material accumulation process during which a accumulation of snow and ice forms or increases in mass."" .

,The snow and ice accumulation process is identified as a type of hydrological process and is characterized by several key aspects. It shares similarities with a material accumulation process and specifically intersects with processes that result in the formation of a mass of ice and snow. This process is also described as an intersection of snow accumulation and ice accumulation processes, where each contributes to the formation of snow and ice masses. Furthermore, it is recognized for leading to the formation of a significant mass of ice and snow. The process is defined as a material accumulation process during which an accumulation of snow and ice forms or increases in mass.",5,True
:has_definition ""A object which is composed primarily of water-based snow and ice."" .

,A mass of ice and snow is defined as an object primarily composed of water-based snow and ice. It is equivalent to something that intersects compounded environmental materials and something primarily composed of an intersection of water ice and snow. This mass is categorized under various types: it is a type of ice mass and also a type of intersection between a snow mass and something that has at least a part of an ice mass. Moreover, it is recognized as a type that is formed as a result of snow and ice accumulation processes and is primarily composed of an intersection of water ice and snow.",6,True
:has_definition ""A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being located within a glacier or ice sheet, between their summer surface or bed."" .

,Englacial is a position characterized by a unique quality. This positional quality is inherent in an entity because of its location within a glacier or ice sheet, specifically between their summer surface or bed. Furthermore, englacial is defined as belonging to a category that intersects with material entities and is located within the combined areas of an ice sheet and glacier.",3,True
:has_definition ""An environmental system process which occurs within a glacier or ice sheet."" .

,Englacial processes are a specific type of environmental system process characterized by their occurrence within glaciers or ice sheets. These processes are defined as those that happen at the intersection of environmental system processes and those processes that take place within the collective environment of an ice sheet or glacier. Additionally, englacial processes are described by their involvement with material entities that possess some quality of being englacial. In essence, an englacial process is understood as an environmental system process which occurs within a glacier or ice sheet, encapsulating interactions with material entities and qualities specific to the englacial context.",5,True
:has_definition ""A glacial surface layer which is present at the point in time where any given part of a glacier reaches its minimum annual mass."" .

,A glacial summer surface is a type of glacial surface layer that is also classified as a type of entity adjacent to some planetary atmosphere. It is defined as a glacial surface layer present at the point in time when any given part of a glacier reaches its minimum annual mass.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001624,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A glacial surface layer which is adjacent to the bedrock or debris over which a glacier flows."" .

,A glacial bed is a type of glacial surface layer and is defined as a glacial surface layer which is adjacent to the bedrock or debris over which a glacier flows. Additionally, a glacial bed is a type of entity that is at least adjacent to an entity that is a union of bedrock and an entity that is an intersection of solid environmental material and an entity that is at least adjacent to a planetary landmass.",3,True
:has_definition ""A tundra ecosystem which is subject to polar climatic conditions."" .

,The polar tundra ecosystem is a type of tundra ecosystem and a type of polar environment, as well as being a type of something that at least overlaps some area of polar tundra. It is defined as a tundra ecosystem which is subject to polar climatic conditions.",4,True
:has_definition ""An ecosystem which is determined by the presence of rounded mineral concretions primarily composed of manganese hydroxides on the seafloor.""

,The polymetallic nodule ecosystem, which is also precisely known as the manganese nodule ecosystem and relatedly referred to as a polymetallic nodule field, is defined as an ecosystem characterized by the presence of rounded mineral concretions primarily composed of manganese hydroxides on the seafloor. This ecosystem is a specific type of sediment environment, marine ecosystem, and part of the sea floor that is determined by the presence of polymetallic nodules.",7,True
:has_definition ""A water flow process during which fresh or brackish groundwater flows from from a landmass into the sea."" .

,The submarine groundwater discharge process is a type of groundwater discharge process that occurs in some marine water body and in some aquifer. This process is defined as a water flow process during which fresh or brackish groundwater flows from a landmass into the sea.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001631,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A water flow process during which water flows out of an aquifer."" .

,The groundwater discharge process is a type of water flow process and is also a type of process that at least has part some groundwater flow. It is defined as a water flow process during which water flows out of an aquifer.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001632,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A water flow process during which water is transported through an aquifer."" .

,Groundwater flow is a type of water flow process that occurs in an aquifer and involves groundwater as a participant. It is defined as a water flow process during which water is transported through an aquifer.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001633,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An environmental pollution process during which contaminants derived from agricultural activity are released into an environmental system.""

,Agricultural pollution is a type of environmental pollution and is specifically an environmental pollution process during which contaminants derived from agricultural activity are released into an environmental system. It occurs in environments that are a combination of cropland and rangeland biomes. Moreover, agricultural pollution is exactly synonymous with ""Verschumutzung durch Landwirtschaft.""",4,True
:has_definition ""An active agri-ecosystem management process during which the variability of land use types or the spatial structure of land under agricultural production is increased.""

,The agricultural landscape diversification process is a type of active agri-ecosystem management process. It is defined as an active agri-ecosystem management process during which the variability of land use types or the spatial structure of land under agricultural production is increased. Additionally, the agricultural landscape diversification process has an exact synonym, Agrarlandschaftsdiversifizierung.",3,True
:has_definition ""A conservation process during which the variability of life - from genes to ecosystems - is preserved."" .

,The biodiversity conservation process is a type of conservation that is an active ecosystem management process. It is defined as a conservation process during which the variability of life - from genes to ecosystems - is preserved.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001636,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A biodiversity conservation process during which the variability of insect communities, or parts thereof, is preserved."" .

,The insect conservation process falls under the category of biodiversity conservation processes. It specifically focuses on activities that involve entities that are both part of an ecological community and primarily composed of insects. The definition of the insect conservation process is a biodiversity conservation process aimed at preserving the variability of insect communities or parts thereof.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001637,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An active agri-ecosystem management process during which an ecosystem is modified for the production of one or a small collection of crops or other agricultural products.""

,The agricultural specialization process is a type of active agri-ecosystem management process. It is defined as an active agri-ecosystem management process during which an ecosystem is modified for the production of one or a small collection of crops or other agricultural products. This process also has the exact synonym ""Spezialisierung der Landwirtschaft.""",3,True
:has_definition ""Soil in which segregated ice will form (causing frost heave) under the required conditions of moisture supply and temperature."" .

,Frost susceptible soil is a type of soil defined as soil in which segregated ice will form (causing frost heave) under the required conditions of moisture supply and temperature.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001639,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
""formation of a solid aerosol in an atmosphere"",
""formation of a solid aerosol in the atmosphere""
:has_definition ""A process during which microscopic solid particulates are formed from liquid materials in an atmosphere.""
:has_exact_synonym ""formation of solid particles from liquid material in an atmosphere"" .

,The formation of a solid aerosol from liquid material in an atmosphere is identical to an intersection of processes, including the formation of a solid aerosol in an atmosphere and processes that both input some liquid environmental material and output aerosolized solids. This specific formation is categorized under the broader types of both the formation of a solid aerosol in an atmosphere and processes that require the input of some liquid environmental material. It is defined as a process during which microscopic solid particulates are formed from liquid materials in an atmosphere. Moreover, this formation is broadly synonymous with the atmospheric formation of a solid aerosol, the formation of a solid aerosol in an atmosphere, and the formation of a solid aerosol in the atmosphere. It also has an exact synonym: the formation of solid particles from liquid material in an atmosphere.",8,True
:has_definition ""A process during which supercooled water droplets in a cloud freeze into ice crystals."" .

,Glaciation of water droplets in a cloud, also broadly known as glaciation, is a type of formation of a solid aerosol from liquid material in an atmosphere and a hydrological process. This process is characterized by at least a part of the freezing of water into water ice, occurring in water-based clouds. It involves water-based cloud droplets as inputs and results in the formation of water ice crystals as outputs. Essentially, glaciation of water droplets in a cloud is defined as a process during which supercooled water droplets in a cloud freeze into ice crystals.",8,True
:has_definition ""An interval of time within an ice age and during which temperatures fall resulting in planet-wide glacier advances.""

,Glaciation is a type of one-dimensional temporal region, and it is part of at least some ice age, also having at least some part of glacial ice gain. It is defined as an interval of time within an ice age during which temperatures fall, resulting in planet-wide glacier advances. Glaciation is broadly synonymous with ""glacial"" and has exact synonyms such as ""glacial period"" and ""glacierisation.""",7,True
:has_definition ""An interval of time within an ice age and during which temperatures rise and result in planet-wide glacier retreat.""

,Interglacial is a type of one-dimensional temporal region that is part of an ice age and involves significant glacial ice loss. It is defined as an interval of time within an ice age during which temperatures rise, resulting in a planet-wide retreat of glaciers. Moreover, interglacial is exactly synonymous with the term interglacial period.",5,True

:has_definition ""A temporal interval during which a planet's surface and atmospheric temperatures fall, resulting in the presence or expansion of continental and polar ice sheets or alpine glaciers."" .

,An ice age is a type of one-dimensional temporal region defined as a temporal interval during which a planet's surface and atmospheric temperatures fall, resulting in the presence or expansion of continental and polar ice sheets or alpine glaciers.",2,True

,Material primarily composed of biogenic carbonates is identical to something that is both an environmental material and at least primarily composed of substances that are an intersection of carbonates and those formed as a result of some biological process. Furthermore, material primarily composed of biogenic carbonates is classified as a type of environmental material. It is also considered a type of material that is at least primarily composed of substances that are an intersection of carbonates and those formed as a result of some biological process.",3,True
:has_definition ""That part of an atmosphere which is composed of gaseous material."" .

,The gaseous part of an atmosphere is defined as that part of an atmosphere which is composed of gaseous material. It is identical to something that intersects with a gaseous astronomical body part and something that is at least a part of some atmosphere. Furthermore, the gaseous part of an atmosphere is categorized as a type of gaseous astronomical body part and also as a type of something that is at least part of some atmosphere.",4,True
:has_definition ""A solid material which does not have a regularly organised internal structure."" .

,An amorphous solid is defined as a solid material that does not have a regularly organized internal structure. It is considered the same as something that intersects with both a solid environmental material and something that, at the very least, has qualities of being either amorphous or unstructured. Moreover, an amorphous solid is categorized as a type of solid environmental material and as a type of entity that possesses qualities of being amorphous or unstructured.",4,True
:has_definition ""A colloidal suspension which is dispersed through a part of a hydrosphere."" .

,A colloid suspended in a hydrosphere is defined as a colloidal suspension that is dispersed through a part of a hydrosphere. This concept is equivalent to the intersection of a colloidal suspension and something that is at least part of some hydrosphere. Furthermore, a colloid suspended in a hydrosphere is considered a type of colloidal suspension as well as a type of entity that is at least part of some hydrosphere.",4,True
:has_definition ""Colloidal sediment which is suspended in a part of the hydrosphere."" .

,Suspended colloidal sediment is a type of colloid that is primarily composed of colloidal sediment and is suspended in a hydrosphere. It is defined as colloidal sediment which is suspended in a part of the hydrosphere.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001649,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An environmental material which is denser than bromoform."" .

,Heavy fraction material is a type of environmental material defined as an environmental material that is denser than bromoform.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001650,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An environmental material which is less dense than bromoform."" .

,Light fraction material is a type of environmental material defined as an environmental material which is less dense than bromoform.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001651,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""Waterborne particulate matter which is part of a hydrosphere.""@en .

,Particulate matter in a hydrosphere is defined as waterborne particulate matter and is a type of particulate matter that is surrounded by water and is part of the hydrosphere. This categorization emphasizes that particulate matter in a hydrosphere is intricately linked to the environment where water intersects with various elements of the hydrosphere.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001652,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An aerosol that is suspended in an atmosphere."" .

,Atmospheric aerosol is defined as an aerosol that is suspended in an atmosphere, which is the same as something that is both an aerosol and at least partly part of some atmosphere. Additionally, atmospheric aerosol is identified as a type of aerosol and also as a type of entity that is at least part of some atmosphere.",4,True

:has_definition ""An estuary in which mixing by tidal forcing exceeds the force of riverine output, resulting in thorough homogenisation of the estuary's water column and the disappearance of a vertical salinity gradient and the freshwater-seawater boundary."" .

,A well-mixed estuary is a type of estuary defined as an estuary in which mixing by tidal forcing exceeds the force of riverine output. This results in thorough homogenization of the estuary's water column and the disappearance of a vertical salinity gradient and the freshwater-seawater boundary.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001654,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A material transformation process during which solid or liquid particles form and are suspended in a mass of air, thus creating an aerosol."" .

,The aerosol formation process is a material transformation process during which solid or liquid particles form and are suspended in a mass of air, creating an aerosol. This process is similar to the intersection of a material transformation process and a process that at least produces some aerosol as output. Furthermore, the aerosol formation process is classified as a type of process that includes, at least in part, the formation of aerosolized particles and as a type that results in the output of some aerosol.",5,True
:has_definition ""An environmental process which involves glaciers or ice sheets."" .

,A glacial process is identical to an environmental system process that intersects with processes that involve, at a minimum, participants that are either ice sheets, glaciers, or a combination of both. Additionally, a glacial process is categorized under environmental system processes. It is also defined as a type of process that necessarily involves participants that could be either an ice sheet, a glacier, or both. Moreover, a glacial process has the definition: an environmental process which involves glaciers or ice sheets.",4,True
:has_definition ""A glacial ice loss process during which the snout (toe) of a glacier shrinks following successive years of negative mass balance.""

,Glacial retreat is a type of glacial ice loss and has an exact synonym, glacier retreat. It is defined as a glacial ice loss process during which the snout (toe) of a glacier shrinks following successive years of negative mass balance. Glacial retreat is also characterized by involving at least a part of a process that is a combination of melting, sublimation, glacial ice ablation, and glacial ice calving processes.",4,True
:has_definition ""An ice calving process during which a mass of ice falls from a larger mass onto land."" .

,Calving of ice onto land is defined as an ice calving process during which a mass of ice falls from a larger mass onto land. This process is a type of ice calving and also a type of event that involves at least some planetary landmass as a participant.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001658,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An ice calving process during which a mass of ice falls from a larger mass into a body of water."" .

,Calving of ice into water is classified as a type of ice calving process and also as a type of process that necessarily involves some water body as a participant. It is defined as an ice calving process during which a mass of ice falls from a larger mass into a body of water.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001659,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A frost action process which occurs in cold environments which are not part of a glacier.""

,A periglacial process is a type of frost action process, defined as a frost action process that occurs in cold environments which are not part of a glacier. It is also related to the synonym periglaciation.",3,True

:has_definition ""A material transport process during which alternate freezing and thawing of moisture in soil, rock and other materials results  modifications of those materials and in the formation of structures on, or in, the ground."" .

,The frost action process is a type of water flow process that involves at least some part of the freezing of water into ice and encompasses a process that is the union of melting and thawing. It is defined as a material transport process during which the alternate freezing and thawing of moisture in soil, rock, and other materials lead to modifications of those materials and in the formation of structures on, or in, the ground.",4,True
:has_definition ""A frost action process during which objects embedded in the ground are cumulatively displaced upwards."" .
,Frost jacking, a type of cryoturbation of soil, is defined as a frost action process during which objects embedded in the ground are cumulatively displaced upwards.",2,True
:has_definition ""A frost action process during which the soil particles are differentially displaced according to their size ranges."" .
,Frost sorting is a type of cryoturbation of soil, defined as a frost action process during which the soil particles are differentially displaced according to their size ranges.",2,True

:has_definition ""A frost action process during which the pressure of water freezing in cracks, crevices, pores, joints or bedding planes results in the mechanical disintegration, splitting or break-up of rock."" .

,Frost wedging is a type of cryoturbation of soil and is defined as a frost action process during which the pressure of water freezing in cracks, crevices, pores, joints, or bedding planes results in the mechanical disintegration, splitting, or break-up of rock.",2,True
:has_definition ""A frost action process during which soil is displaced."" .

,Cryoturbation of soil is a type of frost action process that involves soil as a participant and results in soil cryoturbate as its output. It is defined as a frost action process during which soil is displaced.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001665,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A mass of soil moved or disturbed by frost action."" .

,Soil cryoturbate is a type of solid astronomical body part and is also a type of entity that results from the output of some cryoturbation of soil. It is defined as a mass of soil moved or disturbed by frost action.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001666,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A water flow process which comprises a sudden‐onset high‐magnitude discharge of water and sediment from a glacial source""

,Glacial run refers to a specific type of water flow process characterized by a sudden-onset, high-magnitude discharge of water and sediment originating from a glacial source. This process involves the interaction with environmental materials, notably those that are a combination of materials composed primarily of liquid water and those containing sediments. Participants in this process include entities that are part of a group combining both proglacial and subglacial lakes. Glacial run is also precisely known by several synonyms: Jokuelhlaup, Jokulhlaup, and Jökulhlaup, highlighting its significance and recognition in various contexts.",7,True
rdf:rest [ rdf:first [ owl:unionOf [ rdf:first [ a owl:Restriction
:has_definition ""A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being derived from, part of, or otherwise dependent on the seas or oceans."" .

,Thalassic is a type of physical quality. It is characterized by being at least partly derived from, located in, or a part of marine water bodies, specifically where it intersects with continuants and unions involving entities that are derived from, part of, or located in marine water bodies. Furthermore, thalassic is defined by the physical quality inherent in a bearer due to the bearer's derivation from, part of, or dependence on the seas or oceans.",3,True
:has_definition ""An environmental zone which contains a weather front, bounded by frontal surfaces.""@en .

,An atmospheric frontal zone is a type of environmental zone that is characterized by containing at least some weather front. It is defined as an environmental zone which contains a weather front, bounded by frontal surfaces. Additionally, the atmospheric frontal zone is broadly synonymous with ""frontal zone.""",4,True
:has_definition ""An aquaculture process during which marine organisms are cultivated in the open ocean, an enclosure in the ocean, or in tanks, ponds or raceways which are filled with seawater.""

,The mariculture process is a type of aquaculture, hydrological process, and it also relates to processes that occur in open cage mariculture facilities and involve sea water as a participant. Furthermore, mariculture, also known as mariculture, is defined as an aquaculture process during which marine organisms are cultivated in the open ocean, an enclosure in the ocean, or in tanks, ponds, or raceways filled with seawater.",6,True

:has_definition ""A mariculture process during which organisms are cultivated in cages which allow the passage of materials such as wastes, pathogens, antibiotics, and - should a containment breach occur - cultivated organisms themselves to and from the surrounding marine environment."" .

,The open cage mariculture process is a type of mariculture process. It is defined as a mariculture process during which organisms are cultivated in cages. These cages allow the passage of materials such as wastes, pathogens, antibiotics, and, should a containment breach occur, cultivated organisms themselves to and from the surrounding marine environment.",2,True
:has_definition ""A construction which contains the equipment needed to perform mariculture in open cages - permitting the exchange of material with the surrounding marine water."" .

,An open cage mariculture facility is a type of human construction that encompasses a specific process known as open cage mariculture. This facility is uniquely positioned in locations that are either marine water bodies, marine water masses, or at the intersection of sea water and depressed landforms. It is defined as a construction equipped with the necessary tools to conduct mariculture within open cages, allowing for the free exchange of materials with the surrounding marine waters.",4,True
:has_definition ""A gaseous surface layer which is composed of the warmer air mass(es) along the horizontal density and temperature discontinuity in a weather front.""@en .

,The frontal surface of a weather front is a type of atmospheric layer, gaseous surface layer, and part of a weather front that has characteristics of increased temperature. It is adjacent to an intersection of an air mass that possesses a quality of decreased temperature. Moreover, the frontal surface of a weather front is defined as a gaseous surface layer composed of the warmer air masses along the horizontal density and temperature discontinuity in a weather front. Additionally, the frontal surface of a weather front is broadly synonymous with the term ""frontal surface.""",7,True
:has_definition ""A surface layer which is composed primarily of some liquid or gas.""@en .

,The fluid surface layer is defined as a surface layer which is primarily composed of some liquid or gas. It is identical to the intersection of a surface layer and something that is at least composed primarily of the union of gaseous environmental material and liquid environmental material. Additionally, the fluid surface layer is classified as a type of surface layer as well as a type of fluid interface layer.",4,True
:has_definition ""A cline across which one or more solid environmental materials dissolve into their surrounding fluid."" .

,Lysocline is a type of fluid cline and is defined as a cline across which one or more solid environmental materials dissolve into their surrounding fluid.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001675,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A cline across which nutrient content of a fluid changes rapidly."" .

,A nutricline is a type of fluid cline defined as a cline across which the nutrient content of a fluid changes rapidly.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001676,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A cline which is part of a marine water body."" .

,A marine cline is defined as a cline which is part of a marine water body, and it represents the intersection of a fluid cline with at least a part of a marine water body. Furthermore, a marine cline is classified as a type of fluid cline and also as a type of entity that is at least partly encompassed by a marine water body.",4,True

:has_definition ""A surface layer which separates two portions of fluid with respect to either 1) a discontinuity of some fluid property or 2) some derivative of one of these properties in a direction normal to the interface."" .

,The fluid interface layer is the same as something that represents the intersection of an interface layer and something that is at least composed primarily of a union of gaseous environmental material and liquid environmental material. Additionally, the fluid interface layer is categorized as a type of fluid layer as well as a type of interface layer. Furthermore, the fluid interface layer is defined as a surface layer which separates two portions of fluid with respect to either a discontinuity of some fluid property or some derivative of one of these properties in a direction normal to the interface.",4,True
:has_definition ""A layer which is composed primarily of some fluid."" .

,The fluid layer is equivalent to an intersection of a layer and something that is at least composed primarily of a union of gaseous environmental material and liquid environmental material. It is a specific type of layer and also falls under the category of being primarily composed of a mixture of gaseous and liquid environmental materials. Additionally, the fluid layer is defined as a layer which is primarily composed of some type of fluid.",4,True
:has_definition ""A fluid interface which separates two fluid masses with differing properties."" .
,A fluid front is a type of fluid interface layer, defined as a fluid interface that separates two fluid masses with differing properties.",2,True
:has_definition ""A fluid front which is composed primarily of gaseous material and separates at least two gaseous masses."" .

,A gaseous front is defined as a fluid front that is composed primarily of gaseous material and serves to separate at least two gaseous masses. It is identified as a type of fluid front and also as a type that is at least composed primarily of some gaseous environmental material. Additionally, a gaseous front is equivalent to something that intersects with both a fluid front and something that is at least composed primarily of some gaseous environmental material.",4,True
:has_definition ""A gaseous front which separates two masses of air with different densities and is a principal cause of meteorological phenomena.""

,A weather front is identified as the intersection of a gaseous front and an entity that is at least partially part of an atmosphere, and it is also primarily composed of air. It is categorized under various types, including an atmospheric layer, a gaseous front, and entities that are fundamentally composed of air. Additionally, a weather front is recognized as a causal agent in atmospheric processes and as a configuration that has at least two adjacent air masses. It is defined as a gaseous front that separates two masses of air with different densities and is a principal cause of meteorological phenomena. Furthermore, a weather front is exactly synonymous with a meteorological front.",8,True
:has_definition ""An object which is composed of a continuous mass of air."" .

,An air mass is equivalent to an entity that is an intersection of a mass of gas and an entity that is at least composed primarily of air. It is a type of mass of gas and also a type of entity that is at least composed primarily of air. Furthermore, an air mass is defined as an object which is composed of a continuous mass of air.",4,True
:has_definition ""A fluid surface layer which is composed primarily of some gaseous material.""@en .

,The gaseous surface layer is defined as a fluid surface layer composed primarily of some gaseous material. It is a type of fluid surface layer and also a type that is at least composed primarily of some gaseous environmental material. Additionally, the gaseous surface layer is the same as the intersection of a fluid surface layer and something that is at least composed primarily of some gaseous environmental material.",4,True

:has_definition ""A layer which separates two portions of environmental material which possess 1) differing compositions, 2) a discontinuity of some property, or 3) some derivative of some property in a direction normal to the interface.""@en .

,The interface layer is a type of layer that is defined as a layer which separates two portions of environmental material. These portions possess differing compositions, a discontinuity of some property, or some derivative of some property in a direction normal to the interface.",2,True
